    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This geometry source’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometrysource/1523071-semantic"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property must be "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometrysourcesemanticboneweights"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Its data is an array of floating-point vectors, whose "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometrysource/1522832-componentspervector"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " count is the number of bones influencing each vertex. Each vector corresponds to a vertex in the geometry’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometrysourcesemanticvertex"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " geometry source, and each component in a vector specifies the influence of a bone on that vertex’s position. The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnskinner/1524117-boneindices"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " source determines which nodes in the bones array correspond to each component in the vector. A component value of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " means that the bone has no influence on that vertex; positive or negative values scale the transformation of a bone node before SceneKit applies that transformation to the vertex."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SceneKit performs skeletal animation on the GPU only if the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scngeometrysource/1522832-componentspervector"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " count in this geometry source is "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "4"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " or less. Larger vectors result in CPU-based animation and drastically reduced rendering performance."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        }
      ]
    }
